{"id": "firmware-development--heltec-v2-rx-problem", "title": "Heltec V2 RX problem", "forum": "firmware-development", "messages": [{"id": "1476682544958275709", "author": "powernet", "author_handle": "powernet_60896", "user_id": "1466207904611832063", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Thursday, February 26, 2026 3:49 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-02-26 3:49 p.m.", "text": "I've a heltec v2 borad and exibit RX problem. In RSSI scope if fresly reset seems ok tested with an signal generator on right frequency, but if I stop signal and restart the RSSI indicator reamin struck on low value (115dBm).I've analayzed the VEXT bus and seems OK, and with a simple arduino program that read rx signal work great. Also with other firmaware like meshcom seems ok. I suppose some problem in TX/RX management or in nsome kind of ACG. I'm not an expret on programming but i've try some mods in firmware without solution. Thank a lot to who help me. Alessandro IW5CRK", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>I&#39;ve a heltec v2 borad and exibit RX problem. In RSSI scope if fresly reset seems ok tested with an signal generator on right frequency, but if I stop signal and restart the RSSI indicator reamin struck on low value (115dBm).I&#39;ve analayzed the VEXT bus and seems OK, and with a simple arduino program that read rx signal work great. Also with other firmaware like meshcom seems ok. I suppose some problem in TX/RX management or in nsome kind of ACG. I&#39;m not an expret on programming but i&#39;ve try some mods in firmware without solution. Thank a lot to who help me. Alessandro IW5CRK</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1476683013340270795", "author": "gjelsoe", "author_handle": "cossie1413", "user_id": "297128333332709377", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/297128333332709377/d677b018cc6072f37763a51d37bb76f1.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Thursday, February 26, 2026 3:51 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-02-26 3:51 p.m.", "text": "Did you set GPIO26 to LOW?", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Did you set GPIO26 to LOW?</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1476684185010835617", "author": "powernet", "author_handle": "powernet_60896", "user_id": "1466207904611832063", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Thursday, February 26, 2026 3:55 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-02-26 3:55 p.m.", "text": "in firmware configuration ?", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>in firmware configuration ?</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": ["<div class=chatlog__attachment><div class=chatlog__attachment-generic><svg class=chatlog__attachment-generic-icon><use href=#attachment-icon /></svg><div class=chatlog__attachment-generic-name><a href=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1476682544958275709/1476684184708976792/WIFI_LoRa_32_V2868-915_1.pdf?ex=69ebd8d1&amp;is=69ea8751&amp;hm=c2bdcd74497266f6af930dcb7c76339d997ab0c860dc9f454eb6e301495cdef6&amp;\"> WIFI_LoRa_32_V2868-915_1.pdf </a></div><div class=chatlog__attachment-generic-size>132.84 KB</div></div></div>"], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1476689199896985810", "author": "gjelsoe", "author_handle": "cossie1413", "user_id": "297128333332709377", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/297128333332709377/d677b018cc6072f37763a51d37bb76f1.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Thursday, February 26, 2026 4:15 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-02-26 4:15 p.m.", "text": "Sorry, should have been GPIO21 not GPIO26", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Sorry, should have been GPIO21 not GPIO26</span></div>", "em