, "author_handle": "cossie1413", "user_id": "297128333332709377", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/297128333332709377/d677b018cc6072f37763a51d37bb76f1.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Saturday, February 28, 2026 2:49 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-02-28 2:49 a.m.", "text": "https://www.semtech.com/products/wireless-rf/lora-connect/sx1278", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve><a href=\"https://www.semtech.com/products/wireless-rf/lora-connect/sx1278\">https://www.semtech.com/products/wireless-rf/lora-connect/sx1278</a></span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1478161198737395784", "author": "powernet", "author_handle": "powernet_60896", "user_id": "1466207904611832063", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Monday, March 2, 2026 5:44 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-03-02 5:44 p.m.", "text": "no step away with heltec V2 (clone?). Tx work Rx no", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>no step away with heltec V2 (clone?). Tx work Rx no</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1493975498244620351", "author": "powernet", "author_handle": "powernet_60896", "user_id": "1466207904611832063", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Wednesday, April 15, 2026 10:05 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-04-15 10:05 a.m.", "text": "you are right! 22Khz of frequency drift. Meshtastic works because use a higher BW. Thak you so much!", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>you are right! 22Khz of frequency drift. Meshtastic works because use a higher BW. Thak you so much!</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=thumbsup><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=👍 src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f44d.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>1</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1001187579221254155/5093cda953085e66201d8a617dc03e77.png?size=512\" alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author style=color:rgb(31,139,76) title=mikesallotment>Mike&#x27;s Allotment</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1480887002558627911')\"> The existing MC Heltec V2 firmware works fine - so you shouldn&#39;t be needing to change anything.  There is a known &#39;feature&#39; with the sx1276 radio where it suffers from frequency shift/offset depending on which radio params you&#39;re using.\n\nI&#39;ve posted many times previously about this - just search for posts by me with Heltec V2.\n\nBasically you might just need to configure the frequency slightly higher.\n\nMight not be your issue, but worth a try... </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1493977764561293312", "author": "powernet", "author_handle": "powernet_60896", "user_id": "1466207904611832063", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Wednesday, April 15, 2026 10:14 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-04-15 10:14 a.m.", "text": "I chose the narrow BW available and moved the frequency at step of 1KHz for finding upper and lower limit of reception with a reapeter setted at same BW. The move at the center and reopen BW.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>I chose the narrow BW available and moved the frequency at step of 1KHz for finding upper and lower limit of reception with a reapeter setted at same BW. The move at the center and reopen BW.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}]}